## 4. Four-strategy scoring rubric (0–100 each)

State equity assumptions explicitly. Cap 100, floor 0.

**Equity estimation:** estate/probate 70–100% assessed; tax-lien firm foreclosing 60–100%; sale ≤4y + bank LP ~8% equity left; sale 5–10y 20–35%; sale >10y 40–70%; no sale data 0–30% conservative.

**A — Cash wholesale / flip:** +25 sale >10y, +10 sale 5–10y, +15 yr<1980, +20 active LP/lien, +15 tax-lien firm, +20 probate, +10 Zillow as-is keywords, +10 absentee, +15 equity>35%, −20 equity<10%. ≥70 = strong wholesale.

**B — Sub-to / creative:** +30 sale 2020–22, +15 sale 2023–24, +25 bank LP (PennyMac, Freedom, Truist, etc.), +20 equity 5–25%, +10 sale ≥$300k, +10 premium sub, −15 tax-lien firm, −10 probate. ≥70 = sub-to.

**C — FHA 203k (Emily/Ethan personal):** +20 yr<1990, +20 premium/historic, +20 sale >7y, +15 distress, +20 probate, +15 as-is keywords, −20 recent low equity, −10 sale >$500k. ≥70 = manual Telegram review only — **never auto-mailer**.

**D — Short sale:** +25 bank LP, +25 sale 2021–23, +20 equity<10%, +30 underwater (replaces <10%), +10 sale ≈ assessed, +10 premium sub, −20 tax-lien firm, −15 probate. ≥70 = short sale handoff.

**Premium Scott subs:** Cherry Blossom Village, Canewood, Mallard Point, Bradford Place, Adena Ridge, Mount Vernon, Thoroughbred Acres, Abbey at Old Oxford, Peninsula, Ironworks Estate, Sutton Place, Paynes Landing, Elkhorn Green/Meadows, Whistler Estates, Pleasant Valley, Homestead Village, Etter Woods, Lancaster Heights, Rocky Creek Farm, Moonlake. Historic: Paynes Addition, Brickwood, Bourbon St corridor, Maddox, Payne, Montgomery, Flinn Court.

Code also implements scores in `scraper-service/app/pipeline/investment_scorer.py` and `creative_finance_signals.py` — prefer live JSON fields when present.

## 5. List stacking (rapid-fire wholesaler core)

Properties on **3+ lists = HOT**, 2 = WARM, 1 = COLD. Conversion ~5–8% vs 1–2% single-list.

| # | List | Status |
|---|------|--------|
| 1 | Tax delinquent | ✅ actionable MD per county |
| 2 | Pre-foreclosure LP | ✅ portal-intel (Scott+ growing) |
| 3 | Absentee owner | ⚠️ PVA enrich per-lead, not a list yet |
| 4 | High equity | ⚠️ derivable, not automated |
| 5 | City liens | ⚠️ in scenario library, not isolated |
| 6 | Vacant | ❌ FOIA water shutoff in flight — see `docs/FOIA-WATER-SHUTOFF.md` |
| 7 | Probate/estate | ✅ POA/fiduciary bucket |
| 8 | Divorce/eviction | ❌ KCOJ broken selectors |

**Implemented:** `scraper-service/app/pipeline/list_stack.py` + `scripts/export-stacked-leads.py` → `exports/stacked-leads/`

**PVA batch:** `scripts/run-pva-enrichment-batch.py` → `app/pipeline/pva_enrichment.py`

**Underwriting:** `app/pipeline/underwriting.py` (condition-adjusted PVA + offer bands)

**24h playbook:** `docs/VETERAN-WHOLESALER-PLAYBOOK.md`

**Build order:** PVA enrich Scott/Woodford → stack overlay → high-equity derive → KCOJ civil fix.

## 6. Widening beyond current pipeline

**Tier 1 public records:** KCOJ civil, probate calendars, Master Commissioner auctions, bankruptcy PACER, USPS vacancy (BatchData), Georgetown code enforcement.

**Tier 2 behavioral:** tired landlord (multi-prop + eviction), senior downsize, MLS expired/withdrawn 30–90d, free-and-clear 10+ yr.

**Tier 3 outbound:** SmarterContact SMS, Ballpoint/OpenLetter mail, ringless VM, Mojo dialer + BatchData skip trace.

## 7. Operational rules

**Don't:** parallel eCCLIX sessions; pursue sub-$100 tax bills; raw acreage without PVA structure confirm; auto-outreach 203k path; invent counts; recommend underwater contract without short-sale framing.

**Do:** stack lists before recommending action; state equity assumptions; note data gaps; use scenario buckets when present; prioritize LP >60 days old (KY auction clock 4–9 months).

